==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] [[γεωμετρία]] (geometría), geometry, land-survey, from [[γεωμετρέω]] (geometréo), to practise or to profess geometry, to measure, to survey land, from [[γαία]] (gaía), earth, land, country + [[μετρέω]] (metréo) to measure, to count

===Pronunciation===
*[[SAMPA]]: /dZi."A.m@.tri/
===Noun===
{{en-noun|geometries|-}}

#{{mathematics}} {{uncountable}}} The branch of [[mathematics]] dealing with spatial relationships.
#{{mathematics}} {{countable}} A type of geometry with particular properties.
#:''spherical geometry''
#{{uncountable}} The spatial attributes of an object, etc.

